    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="472"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d472">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.6363/40</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Williams</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1921</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">B.I.A. 5627–93</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    State Department letters of January 7th and January 28th,<note n="43"
                        xml:id="d472fn43">Neither printed.</note> inclosing copies of cablegram to
                    the American Legation at The Hague<note n="44" xml:id="d472fn44">No. 613, Dec.
                        31, 1920, 2 p.m., <ref target="#pg_547">p. 547</ref>.</note> and the
                    American Minister’s reply<note n="45" xml:id="d472fn45">No. 418, Jan. 4, 1921,
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note> relative to the Philippine oil land
                    leasing law.</p>
                <p>I am pleased to inform you that this matter has been brought to the attention of
                    the Governor-General of the Philippine Islands by cable, and it is thought that
                    the desired modification of the oil land leasing Act of the Philippine
                    Government will be brought about. The Governor-General has also been furnished
                    copies of the correspondence relating to this matter.</p>
                <p>Very respectfully,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. R. Williams</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
